        "URL": "data:text/html;charset=utf-8,%3C!doctype%20html%3E%0A%3Chtml%20lang%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Chead%3E%0A%20%20%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctitle%3EAbout%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress%3C%2Ftitle%3E%0A%3C%2Fhead%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%3Ch1%3ELibrary%20of%20Congress%3C%2Fh1%3E%0A%0A%0A%20%20%20The%20Library%20of%20Congress%2C%20founded%20in%201800%20and%20housed%20in%20a%0Athree-building%20complex%20across%20from%20the%20nation's%20capitol%20in%20Washington%2C%0AD.C.%2C%20is%20a%20storehouse%20for%20knowledge%20and%20an%20active%20center%20for%20research%20and%0Acreativity%20of%20all%20kinds--the%20world's%20largest%20and%20most%20open%20library.%20%20With%0Acollections%20numbering%20close%20to%20100%20million%20items%2C%20it%20includes%20materials%20in%0A460%20languages%3B%20the%20basic%20manuscript%20collections%20of%2023%20Presidents%20of%20the%0AUnited%20States%2C%20and%20the%20papers%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20figures%20who%20have%0Ashaped%20history%3B%20maps%20and%20atlases%20that%20have%20aided%20explorers%20and%0Anavigators%20in%20charting%20both%20the%20world%20and%20outer%20space%3B%20the%20earliest%0Amotion%20pictures%20and%20examples%20of%20recorded%20sound%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20latest%0Adata%20bases%20and%20software%20packages.%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20The%20Russian%2FSoviet%20collections%20of%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress%20are%20strong%0Ain%20all%20areas%20except%20clinical%20medicine%20and%20technical%20agriculture%2C%20which%20are%0Acovered%20by%20the%20National%20Library%20of%20Medicine%20and%20the%20National%0AAgricultural%20Library%2C%20respectively.%20%20The%20Library%20possesses%20approximately%0Aone%20million%20volumes%20of%20monographs%20and%20bound%20periodicals%20in%20the%20Russian%0Alanguage%2C%2060%2C000%20in%20Ukrainian%2C%20and%2011%2C000%20in%20Belorussian%2C%20the%20largest%0Acollections%20anywhere%20outside%20Russia.%20%20%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20Library%20acquires%0Aon%20an%20annual%20basis%20some%2015%2C000-20%2C000%20monographs%20and%203%2C000%20serial%0Atitles%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20maintains%20an%20acquisition%20office%20in%0AMoscow.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20The%20Library%20serves%20as%20the%20basic%20research%20arm%20of%20the%20Congress%0Athrough%20its%20Congressional%20Research%20Service%2C%20which%20is%20the%20largest%20public%0Apolicy%20%22think%20tank%22%20in%20America%20and%20annually%20answers%20nearly%20a%0Ahalf-million%20inquiries%20and%20produces%20some%201%2C000%20reports%20for%20the%20Congress.%20%0AThe%20Library%20also%20services%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20nation%20through%20its%0Aadministration%20of%20the%20Copyright%20Office%2C%20the%20National%20Library%20Service%20for%0Athe%20Blind%20and%20Physically%20Handicapped%2C%20the%20Law%20Library%2C%20and%20its%0Aextensive%2C%20multi-lingual%20program%20of%20research%20services.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20In%20servicing%20the%20nation%2C%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress%20also%3A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%0A%20%20%20%3Cli%3E%20%20aids%20other%20libraries%20throughout%20the%20nation%20and%20the%20world%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20by%20cataloging%20new%20publications%20in%20all%20languages%20%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20works%20with%20research%20libraries%20worldwide%20in%20the%20exchange%20of%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20information%20and%20scholarship%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20applies%20new%20technology%20to%20preserve%2C%20restore%2C%20and%20transmit%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20library%20resources%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20documents%20ethnic%20heritage%20in%20its%20folklife%20archives%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20advances%20scholarship%20through%20a%20Council%20of%20Scholars%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20encourages%20reading%20through%20a%20Center%20for%20the%20Book%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20%20documents%20family%20and%20regional%20history%20in%20its%20genealogy%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20collections%0A%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%20produces%20exhibitions%2C%20publications%20and%20public%20programs%0A%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%0A%3Ch2%3EBackground%20and%20History%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%0A%20%20%20The%20Library%20of%20Congress%20is%20the%20nation's%20library.%20%20Its%20services%20extend%0Anot%20only%20to%20members%20and%20committees%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20but%20to%20the%0Aexecutive%20and%20judicial%20branches%20of%20government%2C%20%20to%20libraries%20throughout%0Athe%20nation%20and%20the%20world%2C%20and%20to%20the%20scholars%20and%20researchers%20and%20artists%0Aand%20scientists%20who%20use%20its%20resources.%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20This%20was%20not%20always%20the%20case.%20%20When%20President%20John%20Adams%20signed%0Athe%20bill%20that%20provided%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20seat%20of%20government%20to%20the%0Anew%20capital%20city%20of%20Washington%20in%201800%2C%20he%20created%20a%20reference%20library%20for%0ACongress%20only.%20%20The%20bill%20provided%2C%20among%20other%20items%2C%20%245%2C000%20%22for%20the%0Apurchase%20of%20such%20books%20as%20may%20be%20necessary%20for%20the%20use%20of%20Congress--and%0Afor%20putting%20up%20a%20suitable%20apartment%20for%20containing%20them%20therein....%22%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20The%20first%20books%20were%20ordered%20from%20England%20and%20shipped%20across%20the%0AAtlantic%20in%2011%20hair%20trunks%20and%20a%20map%20case.%20%20The%20Library%20was%20housed%20in%0Athe%20new%20Capitol%20until%20August%201814%2C%20when%20British%20troops%20invaded%0AWashington%20and%20burned%20the%20Capitol%20Building%3B%20the%20small%20congressional%0Alibrary%20of%20some%203%2C000%20volumes%20was%20lost%20in%20the%20fire.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20Within%20a%20month%20former%20President%20Thomas%20Jefferson%2C%20living%20in%0Aretirement%20at%20Monticello%2C%20offered%20as%20a%20replacement%20his%20personal%20library%2C%0Aaccumulated%20over%20a%20span%20of%2050%20years.%20%20It%20was%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%0Afinest%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20%20In%20proffering%20the%20library%20to%20the%20Congress%0AJefferson%20wrote%2C%20%22I%20do%20not%20know%20that%20it%20contains%20any%20branch%20of%20science%0Awhich%20Congress%20would%20wish%20to%20exclude%20from%20their%20collection%3B%20there%20is%2C%20in%0Afact%2C%20no%20subject%20to%20which%20a%20Member%20of%20Congress%20may%20not%20have%20occasion%0Ato%20refer.%22%20%20After%20considerable%20debate%20Congress%20in%20January%201815%20accepted%0AJefferson's%20offer%2C%20appropriating%20%2423%2C950%20for%20the%20collection%20of%206%2C487%20books.%20%0AThus%20the%20foundation%20was%20laid%20for%20a%20great%20national%20library.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20Two%20more%20fires%20were%20to%20influence%20the%20course%20of%20the%20Library%20of%0ACongress.%20%20In%201825%20a%20small%20fire%20in%20the%20Library%20(again%2C%20housed%20in%20rooms%20of%0Athe%20Capitol)%20burned%20some%20duplicate%20volumes.%20%20But%20a%20more%20serious%20fire%20in%0A1851%20destroyed%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20cumulated%20holdings--some%2035%2C000%0Avolumes%2C%20including%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20the%20Jefferson%20library.%20%20In%0Aresponse%2C%20Congress%20voted%20a%20massive%20appropriation%20to%20replace%20the%20lost%0Abooks%2C%20plus%20funds%20to%20construct%20a%20large%2C%20multigalleried%20series%20of%20rooms%0Aacross%20the%20west%20side%20of%20the%20Capitol%20building%2C%20designed%20for%20the%20exclusive%0Ause%20of%20the%20Library.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20By%20the%20close%20of%20the%20Civil%20Way%2C%20the%20collections%20of%20the%20Library%20of%0ACongress%20had%20grown%20to%2082%2C000%20volumes%20and%20were%20still%20principally%20used%20by%0Amembers%20of%20Congress%20and%20committees%3B%20the%20Library%20was%20seen%20mainly%20as%0Athe%20%22Congressional%20Library%2C%22%20as%20it%20was%20popularly%20referred%20to%20into%20the%20early%0Ayears%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EExpanding%20the%20Collections%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20In%201864%20President%20Lincoln%20appointed%20as%20Librarian%20of%20Congress%20a%20man%0Awho%20was%20to%20transform%20the%20Library%20from%20a%20collection%20for%20use%20only%20by%0Amembers%20of%20Congress%2C%20justices%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%0Adiplomatic%20corps%20and%20the%20cabinet.%20%20He%20was%20Ainsworth%20Rand%20Spofford%2C%20who%0Aopened%20the%20Library%20to%20the%20public%20and%20greatly%20expanded%20its%20collections.%20%0ASpofford%20successfully%20advocated%20a%20change%20in%20the%20copyright%20law%20so%20that%20the%0ALibrary%20would%20receive%20two%20free%20copies%20of%20every%20book%2C%20map%2C%20chart%2C%20dramatic%0Aor%20musical%20composition%2C%20engraving%2C%20cut%2C%20print%2C%20or%20photograph%20submitted%0Afor%20copyright.%20%20Through%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20Smithsonian%20Institution%2C%0Ahe%20also%20began%20to%20acquire%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%20American%20scientific%20materials%0Aand%20foreign%20exchange%20documents.%20%20Passage%20of%20another%20law%20resulted%20in%20the%0ALibrary's%20acquisition%20of%20free%20copies%20of%20the%20Congressional%20Record%20and%20all%0AAmerican%20statues%2C%20which%20Spofford%20parlayed%20into%20document%20exchanges%0Awith%20all%20foreign%20countries%20that%20had%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20the%20United%0AStates.%20%20Predictably%2C%20Spofford%20soon%20filled%20all%20the%20Capitol's%20library%20rooms%2C%0Aattics%2C%20and%20hallways.%20%20In%201873%2C%20he%20then%20won%20another%20lobbying%20effort--for%0Aa%20new%20building%20to%20permanently%20house%20the%20nation's%20growing%20collection%20and%0Areading%20rooms%20to%20serve%20scholars%20and%20the%20reading%20public.%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHousing%20the%20Collections%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%20%20%20After%20considering%20and%20rejecting%20designs%20for%20a%20Library%20building%0Aranging%20from%20a%20classic%20Greek%20facade%20to%20Victorian%20Gothic%2C%20a%20congressional%0AJoint%20Committee%20on%20the%20Library%20finally%20selected%20a%20modified%20Italian%0ARenaissance%20style%20submitted%20by%20two%20Washington%20architects%2C%20John%20L.%0ASmithmeyer%20and%20Paul%20J.%20Pelz%2C%20in%20a%20design%20contest.%20%20Frustrated%20by%0Aconstruction%20delays%2C%20however%2C%20Congress%20eventually%20fired%20the%20architects%0Aand%20retained%20Brigadier%20General%20Thomas%20Lincoln%20Casey%2C%20chief%20of%20the%20Army%0AEngineers%2C%20and%20Bernard%20Richard%20Green%2C%20a%20civil%20engineer%2C%20who%20completed%0Athe%20Thomas%20Jefferson%20Building%20in%201897.%20%20A%20celebration%20of%20the%20arts%2C%20their%0A%22American%20Renaissance%22%20creation%20of%20murals%2C%20mosaics%2C%20and%20marble%20was%0Aproduced%20by%20scores%20of%20sculptors%2C%20painters%2C%20and%20stone%20cutters.%20Crowning%0Athe%20structure%20is%20the%20Main%20Reading%20Room's%20glorious%20dome%2C%20125%20feet%20high%0Aand%20100%20feet%20wide%2C%20supported%20by%20marble%20columns%20and%2011-foot%20statues%0Acharacterizing%20%22civilized%20life%20and%20thought.%22%20%20As%20complex%20as%20the%20project%20was%2C%0AGeneral%20Casey%20completed%20the%20Jefferson%20building%20on%20time%20and%20within%20his%0Aoriginal%20budget%20appropriation%20of%20%246.5%20million.%20%20He%20returned%20%24150%2C000%0Aremaining%20in%20the%20building%20fund%20to%20Congress.%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20As%20the%20Library's%20collections%20and%20staff%20continued%20to%20grow%2C%20Congress%0Aadded%20the%20John%20Adams%20Building--designed%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20art%20deco%0Aperiod%20and%20opened%20in%201939--and%20the%20third%20largest%20building%20in%20Washington%2C%0Athe%20James%20Madison%20Memorial%20Building%2C%20which%20opened%20in%201980.%20%20A%20project%0Ato%20renovate%20and%20restore%20the%20Jefferson%20and%20Adams%20buildings%20was%20begun%20in%0A1986%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20six%20years.%20%20The%20project%20includes%0Aupgrading%20all%20heating%2C%20ventilation%2C%20electrical%2C%20and%20plumbing%20facilities%3B%20the%0Arestoration%20and%20repair%20of%20all%20reorganization%20of%20the%20Library's%20diverse%0Acollections%20in%20order%20to%20make%20them%20more%20accessible%20to%20scholars%20and%20the%0Ageneral%20public.%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECataloging%20and%20Using%20the%20Collections%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%20%20%20The%20first%20Librarian%20in%20the%20new%20building%20was%20a%20newspaperman%20with%0Ano%20library%20experience%2C%20John%20Russell%20Young.%20%20He%20quickly%20realized%2C%20however%2C%0Athat%20the%20Library%20had%20to%20get%20control%20of%20collections%20that%20had%20been%20piling%20up%0Aand%20overflowing%20the%20rooms%20in%20the%20Capitol.%20%20Young%20was%20able%20to%20set%20up%0Aorganizational%20units%20and%20devise%20programs%20that%20changed%20the%20Library%20from%0Aessentially%20an%20acquisitions%20operation%20into%20an%20efficient%20processing%20factory%0Athat%20organized%20the%20materials%20and%20made%20them%20useful.%20%20Young%20was%0Asucceeded%20after%20only%20two%20years%20by%20Herbert%20Putnam%2C%20previously%20head%20of%0Athe%20Boston%20Public%20Library%2C%20who%20was%20destined%20to%20be%20Librarian%20of%20Congress%0Afor%2040%20years.%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20While%20Librarian%20Spofford%20had%20collected%20the%20materials%2C%20and%20Young%20had%0Aorganized%20them%2C%20Putnam%20set%20out%20to%20insure%20that%20they%20would%20be%20used.%20%20He%0Atook%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress%20directly%20into%20the%20national%20library%20scene%20and%0Amade%20its%20holdings%20known%20and%20available%20to%20the%20smallest%20community%20library%0Ain%20the%20most%20distant%20part%20of%20the%20country.%20%20The%20familiar%203%22%20x%205%22%20library%20card%0Astemmed%20from%20his%20idea%20of%20cataloging%20books%20as%20quickly%20as%20the%20Library%20of%0ACongress%20received%20them%20via%20copyright%20deposit%20or%20exchange%2C%20and%20then%0Aselling%20the%20resulting%20catalog%20cards%20at%20cost%20to%20local%20libraries.%20%20Thus%20the%0Asmaller%20institutions%20would%20be%20spared%20the%20trouble%20and%20expense%20of%20doing%20the%0Asame%20work%20themselves%20when%20they%20bought%20the%20same%20book.%20%20In%20this%20way%2C%0Athe%20Library%20of%20Congress%20assumed%20a%20leadership%20role%20in%20the%20standardization%0Aof%20cataloging%20practices.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%20Putnam%20organized%20the%20Library's%20services%20to%20the%20blind%2C%20designing%0Aprograms%20that%20at%20first%20loaned%20out%20brailled%20books%20and%20then%20later%20provided%0Aphonograph%20records%20with%20special%20machines%20for%20handicapped%20people.%20%20(The%0Anow-familiar%2033-1%2F3%20rpm%20record%20was%20invented%20for%20Putnam's%20purpose%20and%0Awas%20used%20in%20Library%20of%20Congress%20%22talking%20books%22%20for%2014%20years%20before%20the%0Acommercial%20world%20adopted%20it.)%20%20This%20Library%20of%20Congress%20program%0Acontinues%20to%20open%20word%20windows%20for%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%0Aaround%20the%20nation%2C%20principally%20through%20the%20use%20of%20tape%20cassettes%20and%0Aplayback%20machines.%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ELegislative%20Reference%20Service%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%20%20%20About%201912%20both%20Librarian%20Putnam%20and%20members%20of%20Congress%0Abecame%20concerned%20about%20the%20distance%20that%20was%20widening%20between%20the%0ALibrary%20and%20its%20employer%2C%20the%20Congress.%20%20In%20the%20states%2C%20a%20new%20entity%20had%0Abegun%20to%20emerge%2C%20a%20%22legislative%20reference%20bureau%2C%22%20which%20brought%20together%0Aa%20skilled%20team%20of%20librarians%2C%20economists%2C%20political%20scientists%2C%20and%0Astatisticians%2C%20whose%20only%20purpose%20was%20to%20serve%20the%20legislature%20and%20to%0Arespond%20quickly%20to%20the%20questions%20that%20arose%20in%20the%20legislative%20process.%20%0ACongress%20wanted%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20service%20for%20itself%2C%20and%20Putnam%0Adesigned%20such%20a%20unit%20for%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress.%20%20Called%20the%20Legislative%0AReference%20Service%2C%20it%20went%20into%20operation%20in%201914%20to%20prepare%20indexes%2C%0Adigests%2C%20and%20compilations%20of%20law%20that%20the%20Congress%20might%20need%2C%20but%20it%0Aquickly%20became%20a%20specialized%20reference%20unit%20for%20information%20transfer%20and%0Aresearch.%20%20The%20service%20was%20the%20forerunner%20of%20the%20Library's%20current%2C%0Adistinguished%20Congressional%20Research%20Service.%0A%0A%3Ch3%3EGifts%20to%20the%20Library%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%20%20%20From%20Librarian%20Spofford's%20time%20on%2C%20the%20great%20jewels%20in%20the%0Acollections%20of%20the%20Library%20have%20come%20from%20individual%20Americans%20who%20have%0Agiven%20either%20money%20or%20private%20treasures%20to%20the%20Library%20to%20be%20shared%20with%0Athe%20American%20people.%20%20Traditionally%2C%20the%20routine%20publications%20of%20the%20world%0Ahave%20come%20in%20through%20copyright%20and%20exchange%20programs%2C%20but%20the%20special%2C%0Aunique%2C%20pieces%20have%20come%20as%20private%20gifts.%20%20The%20gift%20of%20the%20Coolidge%0AAuditorium%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Coolidge%20Foundation%20for%20%22the%20study%2C%0Acomposition%2C%20and%20appreciation%20of%20music%22%3B%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Gertrude%0AClarke%20Whittall%20Foundation%20and%20the%20donation%20of%20rare%20Stradivarius%0Ainstruments%20to%20be%20used%20for%20public%20performance%3B%20the%20Lessing%20J.%20Rosenwald%0Acollection%20of%20illustrated%20books%20and%20incunabula%20(books%20published%20in%20the%0Adawn%20of%20printing%2C%20before%201501)%3B%20Joseph%20Pennell's%20gift%20of%20Whistler%0Adrawings%20and%20letters%3B%20the%20private%20papers%20of%20President%20Lincoln%20from%20his%0Ason%2C%20Robert%20Todd%20Lincoln%3B%20and%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20letters%20and%0Adocuments%20from%20musicians%2C%20artists%2C%20writers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20public%20figures%0Aare%20some%20examples%20of%20gifts%20to%20the%20Library%20of%20Congress%20that%20have%20enriched%0Athe%20cultural%20heritage%20of%20the%20nation.%0A%3C%2Fbody%3E%0A%3C%2Fbody%3E%0A%3C%2Fhtml%3E"
